1
00:00:05,063 --> 00:00:07,939
When Guru Mahārāj said that

2
00:00:07,939 --> 00:00:10,004
"There is a science of rāsa

3
00:00:10,805 --> 00:00:13,133
[108 Blue Lotus Flowers]

4
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:15,352
and Rūpa Goswāmī perfectly delineates that

5
00:00:15,352 --> 00:00:16,976
in Bhakti-rāsāmṛta-sindhu.

6
00:00:16,976 --> 00:00:19,028
But anything and all things are possible

7
00:00:19,028 --> 00:00:23,841
in the Absolute, and the Absolute’s devotees

8
00:00:23,841 --> 00:00:28,482
who control the Absolute, if that’s possible

9
00:00:28,482 --> 00:00:31,020
and apparently it is.

10
00:00:31,020 --> 00:00:34,264
Śrī-Kṛṣṇākarṣiṇī cha sā

11
00:00:34,264 --> 00:00:36,320
The Absolute

12
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:39,498
independent supreme reality,

13
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:42,310
the original source of everything

14
00:00:42,310 --> 00:00:46,780
for whom not a blade of grass moves without His will.

15
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:50,773
The supreme omniscient, omnipotent Lord,

16
00:00:50,773 --> 00:00:55,904
personality of Godhead, Svayam Bhagavān

17
00:00:55,904 --> 00:01:01,057
can be controlled through love and devotion.

18
00:01:01,057 --> 00:01:07,719
So, sometimes the science of rāsa  is contradicted.

19
00:01:07,788 --> 00:01:13,413
So, we’re told that previously in Rāmāyaṇa, in Rām-līlā,

20
00:01:13,413 --> 00:01:16,739
when Rām and Lakṣman were in a predicament,

21
00:01:16,739 --> 00:01:19,427
and Hanumān was at his wit's end

22
00:01:22,115 --> 00:01:24,804
and his ability to protect them helped him,

23
00:01:24,804 --> 00:01:27,810
Garuḍa was enlisted,

24
00:01:28,117 --> 00:01:33,910
and Garuḍa performed in flying colors, and at the end,

25
00:01:34,129 --> 00:01:36,588
when it came time for some remuneration,

26
00:01:36,588 --> 00:01:39,722
'dāsa' kari' vetana more deha prema-dhana,

27
00:01:39,722 --> 00:01:43,288
devotees were premic.

28
00:01:43,641 --> 00:01:46,894
Garuḍa is wondering, (to Rāmachandra],

29
00:01:46,894 --> 00:01:52,882
"My Lord, if you can show Your form of Kṛṣṇa.

30
00:01:56,099 --> 00:01:59,531
Remember Kṛṣṇa is akhila-rasāmṛta-mūrtiḥ.

31
00:01:59,531 --> 00:02:03,346
Rām is also His avatār.

32
00:02:04,177 --> 00:02:06,914
It’s Kṛṣṇa playing in a particular way.

33
00:02:06,914 --> 00:02:11,066
And the inverse can be shown to a certain degree.

34
00:02:11,066 --> 00:02:18,482
He said, “But, Garuḍa, Hanumān will become disturbed.”

35
00:02:18,589 --> 00:02:19,899
So, we should be careful

36
00:02:19,899 --> 00:02:25,100
not to disturb the sentiments of other devotees.

37
00:02:25,730 --> 00:02:30,673
No matter how much we think we’re acquainted with reality.

38
00:02:30,673 --> 00:02:31,603
So, Garuḍa said,

39
00:02:31,603 --> 00:02:36,571
“I will, with my wings”,

40
00:02:36,571 --> 00:02:40,500
and actually that's how he had saved them

41
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:46,640
with his mighty wings, making the ocean submit.

42
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:49,137
So he said, “With the same wings that I saved you

43
00:02:49,137 --> 00:02:51,219
I can save you in this situation too.

44
00:02:51,219 --> 00:02:52,974
Hanumān won’t be disturbed,

45
00:02:52,974 --> 00:02:57,627
I’ll make a theatre,

46
00:02:57,934 --> 00:03:01,588
you can show, he won’t see.”

47
00:03:02,410 --> 00:03:05,021
Garuḍa expands his wings,

48
00:03:05,021 --> 00:03:07,631
Ram shows his form of Kṛṣṇa.

49
00:03:07,631 --> 00:03:08,663
Garuḍa is very happy.

50
00:03:08,663 --> 00:03:10,167
Maybe through the wings

51
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:15,465
a little bit Hanumān is seeing something.

52
00:03:15,465 --> 00:03:18,020
And it finishes and Hanumān says,

53
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:28,445
“Garuḍa, someday I’ll exact my revenge." 
 

54
00:03:30,146 --> 00:03:33,585
So, we're told that once in Dvārakā.

55
00:03:33,585 --> 00:03:36,609
All the Pastimes of the Personality of Godhead

56
00:03:36,609 --> 00:03:38,970
are multidimensional.

57
00:03:39,278 --> 00:03:43,492
Kṛṣṇa expresses that He would like

58
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:54,402
to get one hundred and eight blue lotus flowers.

59
00:03:54,402 --> 00:03:55,422
And Garuḍa is there,

60
00:03:55,422 --> 00:03:59,619
"Yes, my Lord. Consider it done."

61
00:03:59,619 --> 00:04:01,421
But these blue lotuses

62
00:04:01,421 --> 00:04:03,436
only grow in a particular place high,

63
00:04:03,436 --> 00:04:07,837
high in the mountains, divine mountains.

64
00:04:07,867 --> 00:04:11,868
So, Garuḍa is flying there to get those,

65
00:04:11,868 --> 00:04:14,374
and when he comes

66
00:04:14,374 --> 00:04:18,133
upon the pathway there is this old, old monkey,

67
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:21,171
lying on the road.

68
00:04:21,417 --> 00:04:25,449
And we know it's a part of Vedic culture,

69
00:04:25,449 --> 00:04:28,673
never to cross over a living being,

70
00:04:28,673 --> 00:04:32,624
because of jīvātmā, Paramātmā.

71
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:35,401
So, we don't even step over a dog or an animal

72
00:04:35,401 --> 00:04:39,211
of any kind out of respect,

73
00:04:39,211 --> 00:04:42,192
jīvātmā, Paramātmā.
 

74
00:04:42,192 --> 00:04:43,643
So, Garuḍa is coming and saying,

75
00:04:43,643 --> 00:04:48,097
"You, monkey, move."

76
00:04:49,893 --> 00:04:56,464
And he's like, "Oh, I am so tired and old, I can't move."

77
00:04:56,464 --> 00:05:00,458
"But I am Garuḍa, the messenger of Vishnu.

78
00:05:00,458 --> 00:05:02,965
And I am on a special mission from Kṛṣṇa

79
00:05:02,965 --> 00:05:05,978
to get one hundred and eight blue lotus flowers.

80
00:05:05,978 --> 00:05:11,404
So monkey, you leave this road and let me cross!"

81
00:05:11,681 --> 00:05:13,349
"Oh, go around me,

82
00:05:13,349 --> 00:05:18,109
I am too much tired and too old."

83
00:05:19,053 --> 00:05:21,455
"Monkey, if you do not move,

84
00:05:21,455 --> 00:05:24,255
then I will blow you away with my wings."

85
00:05:24,255 --> 00:05:26,570
Remember, he made the ocean move,

86
00:05:26,570 --> 00:05:29,258
he can do such things.

87
00:05:29,258 --> 00:05:32,777
"As you wish, Prabhu."

88
00:05:32,777 --> 00:05:35,852
And Garuḍa [imitating sound of the wind].

89
00:05:35,852 --> 00:05:37,879
And the same wings,

90
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:42,007
that could scare the ocean into submission.

91
00:05:42,007 --> 00:05:47,711
We're told, not a hair moved on Hanumān's body.

92
00:05:47,711 --> 00:05:50,856
Wouldn't move one hair.

93
00:05:51,488 --> 00:05:53,952
And rather he reached up,

94
00:05:53,952 --> 00:06:00,257
grabbed Garuḍa and stuffed him under his armpit.

95
00:06:01,426 --> 00:06:05,434
"Hundred and eight blue lotus flowers." 
 

96
00:06:06,987 --> 00:06:10,267
Then Hanumān goes to the mountain, collects

97
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:12,955
the hundred and eight blue lotus flowers,

98
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:16,229
then returns to Dvārakā,

99
00:06:16,783 --> 00:06:18,541
where he is met by Sudarshan.

100
00:06:18,541 --> 00:06:21,145
"Monkey, see the sign,

101
00:06:21,145 --> 00:06:24,184
"No monkeys allowed!"

102
00:06:24,184 --> 00:06:27,411
This is not your place."

103
00:06:27,411 --> 00:06:30,697
"I have one hundred and eight blue lotus flowers

104
00:06:30,697 --> 00:06:32,265
for Lord Kṛṣṇa!"

105
00:06:32,265 --> 00:06:35,354
And Garuḍa is [murmuring].

106
00:06:35,354 --> 00:06:37,688
And Sudarshan, "Monkey, I'm telling you,

107
00:06:37,688 --> 00:06:39,401
no monkeys allowed here!"

108
00:06:39,401 --> 00:06:41,943
And he starts spinning,

109
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:45,133
he's about to finish, and Hanumān raises his hand

110
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:49,634
and Sudarshan becomes a ring on his finger

111
00:06:49,634 --> 00:06:51,481
and he proceeds.

112
00:06:51,481 --> 00:06:54,359
Hundred and eight blue lotus flowers,

113
00:06:54,359 --> 00:06:57,221
Garuḍa, Sudarshan.

114
00:06:58,256 --> 00:07:00,681
And Kṛṣṇa, knowing everything,

115
00:07:00,681 --> 00:07:06,217
He is there with Rukmiṇī and Satyabhāmā and says,

116
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:16,844
"Satyabhāmā, you'll become Sītā and I'll be Rām.

117
00:07:18,056 --> 00:07:19,610
That's will make Hanumān happy."

118
00:07:19,610 --> 00:07:21,668
And Satyabhāmā, "No, no."

119
00:07:21,668 --> 00:07:24,496
Rukmiṇī says "Allright", she agrees.

120
00:07:24,496 --> 00:07:27,777
So, Satyabhāmā hides under the bed,

121
00:07:27,777 --> 00:07:29,890
Rukmiṇī become Sītā,

122
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:31,098
Kṛṣṇa becomes Rām.

123
00:07:31,098 --> 00:07:33,247
Hanumān comes in.

124
00:07:33,247 --> 00:07:38,198
"Rām, Rām, Sītā Rām, Jay Sītā-Rām.

125
00:07:38,198 --> 00:07:44,577
I knew all long my Lord Rām really is Kṛṣṇa."

126
00:07:44,577 --> 00:07:48,860
He presents the hundred and eight blue lotus flowers,

127
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,725
and the Lord says to him,

128
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:57,844
"Hanumān, is there anything I can do for you?

129
00:07:57,844 --> 00:08:00,434
Any desire you have?"

130
00:08:00,434 --> 00:08:03,104
He said, "No, by Your grace everything is well,

131
00:08:03,104 --> 00:08:04,634
but I'm just wondering

132
00:08:04,634 --> 00:08:09,653
who is that, hiding under the bad?"

133
00:08:10,482 --> 00:08:11,745
So, Guru Mahārāj said,

134
00:08:11,745 --> 00:08:15,559
in this instance, Hanumān we take is in Dāsya-rāsa.

135
00:08:15,559 --> 00:08:18,367
He demonstrates his superiority,

136
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:24,508
he checks Garuḍa, Sudarshan,

137
00:08:24,908 --> 00:08:28,476
and even the pride of the Queen Satyabhāmā. 
 

